author: julianfoad
msg: Clarify some code in wc_db.c.  No functional change.
The check_replace_baton struct carried three output parameters from
check_replace_txn(), two through pointers and the third by value.  The test
"(!crb->is_replace_root || !crb->is_replace)" was confusing to me because it
read as if it meant "it is not this kind of replace or not that kind of
replace", whereas in fact it meant "we were not asked for this kind of
replace, or it is not that kind of replace".
(check_replace_baton): Make the 'is_replace' member a pointer like the
others, and rename all three fields with a suffix '_p' to distinguish
them as pointers, since we now need a local non-pointer 'is_replace'
